<TITLE> Justice Matin takes oath as Appellate Division judge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 19 (bdnews24.com) Justice Abdul Matin was sworn in as Appellate Division judge Wednesday. Chief justice M Ruhul Amin supervised the new justice's appointment in the Judges' Lounge. The new justice was appointed by the president under Section 95 of the constitution on September 17. Matin enrolled as a High Court lawyer in 1973 and was appointed an Appellate Division lawyer in 1980 before being promoted to the position of High Court judge in 1996. bdnews24.co
